     Specify the number of bytes â€œcontainedâ€ in a dot, as seen
     throughout the retrieval (1024 by default).  You can postfix the
     value with â€˜kâ€™ or â€˜mâ€™, representing kilobytes and megabytes,
     respectively.  With dot settings you can tailor the dot retrieval
     to suit your needs, or you can use the predefined â€œstylesâ€ (*note
     Download Options::).

