restrict_file_names = unix/windows
     Restrict the file names generated by Wget from URLs.  See
     â€˜--restrict-file-namesâ€™ for a more detailed description.

retr_symlinks = on/off
     When set to on, retrieve symbolic links as if they were plain
     files; the same as â€˜--retr-symlinksâ€™.

retry_connrefused = on/off
     When set to on, consider â€œconnection refusedâ€ a transient errorâ€”the
     same as â€˜--retry-connrefusedâ€™.

robots = on/off
     Specify whether the norobots convention is respected by Wget, â€œonâ€
     by default.  This switch controls both the â€˜/robots.txtâ€™ and the
     â€˜nofollowâ€™ aspect of the spec.  *Note Robot Exclusion::, for more
     details about this.  Be sure you know what you are doing before
     turning this off.

save_cookies = FILE
     Save cookies to FILE.  The same as â€˜--save-cookies FILEâ€™.

save_headers = on/off
     Same as â€˜--save-headersâ€™.

